06917                 return 0x00000300000008BCull;
06918             break;
06919     }
06920     cvmx_warn("CVMX_PCIEEPX_CFG559 (offset = %lu) not supported on this chip\n", offset);
06921     return 0x00000300000008BCull;
06922 }
06923 #else
06924 static inline uint64_t CVMX_PCIEEPX_CFG559(unsigned long offset)
06925 {
06926     switch(cvmx_get_octeon_family()) {
06927         case OCTEON_CN78XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
06928             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX))
06929                 return 0x00000300000008BCull + (offset) * 0x100000000ull;
06930             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX_PASS1_X))
06931                 return 0x00000300000008BCull + (offset) * 0x100000000ull;
06932 
06933         case OCTEON_CN73XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
06934             return 0x00000300000008BCull + (offset) * 0x100000000ull;
06935         case OCTEON_CNF75XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
06936             return 0x00000300000008BCull;
06937     }
06938     return 0x00000300000008BCull;
06939 }
06940 #endif
06941

07892                                                          the other mask bits. */

08132 union cvmx_pcieepx_cfg020 {

08141                                                          software. The number of messages enabled must be less than or equal to the multiple

08146     uint32_t ncp                          : 8;  /**< Next capability pointer. Points to PCI Express capabilities by default, writable through
08147                                                          PEM()_CFG_WR. However, the application must not change this field. */

08149 #else
08150     uint32_t msicid                       : 8;
08151     uint32_t ncp                          : 8;

08158 #endif
08159     } s;

08161 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
08162     uint32_t reserved_24_31               : 8;
08163     uint32_t m64                          : 1;  /**< 64-bit Address Capable, writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR
08164                                                          However, the application must not change this field. */
08165     uint32_t mme                          : 3;  /**< Multiple Message Enabled
08166                                                          Indicates that multiple Message mode is enabled by system
08167                                                          software. The number of Messages enabled must be less than
08168                                                          or equal to the Multiple Message Capable value. */
08169     uint32_t mmc                          : 3;  /**< Multiple Message Capable, writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR
08170                                                          However, the application must not change this field. */
08171     uint32_t msien                        : 1;  /**< MSI Enabled
08172                                                          When set, INTx must be disabled. */
08173     uint32_t ncp                          : 8;  /**< Next Capability Pointer
08174                                                          Points to PCI Express Capabilities by default,
08175                                                          writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR.

08563 /**
08564  * cvmx_pcieep#_cfg030
08565  *
08566  * This register contains the thirty-first 32-bits of PCIe type 0 configuration space.
08567  *
08568  */
08569 union cvmx_pcieepx_cfg030 {
08570     uint32_t u32;
08571     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg030_s {
08572 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
08573     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
08574     uint32_t tp                           : 1;  /**< Transaction pending. Set to 1 when nonposted requests are not yet completed and set to 0
08575                                                          when they are completed. */
08576     uint32_t ap_d                         : 1;  /**< AUX power detected. Set to 1 if AUX power detected. */
08577     uint32_t ur_d                         : 1;  /**< Unsupported request detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or
08578                                                          not error reporting is enabled in the device control register. UR_D occurs when we receive
08579                                                          something unsupported. Unsupported requests are nonfatal errors, so UR_D should cause
08580                                                          NFE_D. Receiving a vendor-defined message should cause an unsupported request. */
08581     uint32_t fe_d                         : 1;  /**< Fatal error detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or not
08582                                                          error reporting is enabled in the device control register. This field is set if we receive
08583                                                          any of the errors in PCIEEP()_CFG066 that has a severity set to fatal. Malformed TLPs
08584                                                          generally fit into this category. */
08585     uint32_t nfe_d                        : 1;  /**< Nonfatal error detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or not
08586                                                          error reporting is enabled in the device control register. This field is set if we receive
08587                                                          any of the errors in PCIEEP()_CFG066 that has a severity set to nonfatal and does not
08588                                                          meet advisory nonfatal criteria, which most poisoned TLPs should. */
08589     uint32_t ce_d                         : 1;  /**< Correctable error detected. Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether or
08590                                                          not error reporting is enabled in the device control register. This field is set if we
08591                                                          receive any of the errors in PCIEEP()_CFG068, for example a replay-timer timeout.
08592                                                          Also, it can be set if we get any of the errors in PCIEEP()_CFG066 that has a severity
08593                                                          set to Nonfatal and meets the Advisory Nonfatal criteria, which most ECRC errors should. */
08594     uint32_t i_flr                        : 1;  /**< Initiate function level reset.
08595                                                          [I_FLR] must not be written to one via the indirect PEM()_CFG_WR. It should only ever
08596                                                          be written to one via a direct PCIe access. */
08597     uint32_t mrrs                         : 3;  /**< Max read request size.
08598                                                          0x0 =128 bytes.
08599                                                          0x1 = 256 bytes.
08600                                                          0x2 = 512 bytes.
08601                                                          0x3 = 1024 bytes.
08602                                                          0x4 = 2048 bytes.
08603                                                          0x5 = 4096 bytes.
08604                                                          SLI_S2M_PORT()_CTL[MRRS] and DPI_SLI_PRT()_CFG[MRRS] must also be set properly.
08605                                                          SLI_S2M_PORT()_CTL[MRRS] and DPI_SLI_PRT()_CFG[MRRS] must not exceed the desired
08606                                                          max read request size. */
08607     uint32_t ns_en                        : 1;  /**< Enable no snoop. */
08608     uint32_t ap_en                        : 1;  /**< AUX power PM enable (not supported). */
08609     uint32_t pf_en                        : 1;  /**< Phantom function enable. This bit should never be set; PEM requests never use phantom functions. */
08610     uint32_t etf_en                       : 1;  /**< Extended tag field enable. */
08611     uint32_t mps                          : 3;  /**< Max payload size. Legal values: 0x0 = 128 B, 0x1 = 256 B.
08612                                                          Larger sizes are not supported by CNXXXX.
08613                                                          DPI_SLI_PRT()_CFG[MPS] must be set to the same value as this field for proper
08614                                                          functionality. */
08615     uint32_t ro_en                        : 1;  /**< Enable relaxed ordering. */
08616     uint32_t ur_en                        : 1;  /**< Unsupported request reporting enable. */
08617     uint32_t fe_en                        : 1;  /**< Fatal error reporting enable. */
08618     uint32_t nfe_en                       : 1;  /**< Nonfatal error reporting enable. */
08619     uint32_t ce_en                        : 1;  /**< Correctable error reporting enable. */
08620 #else
08621     uint32_t ce_en                        : 1;
08622     uint32_t nfe_en                       : 1;
08623     uint32_t fe_en                        : 1;
08624     uint32_t ur_en                        : 1;
08625     uint32_t ro_en                        : 1;
08626     uint32_t mps                          : 3;
08627     uint32_t etf_en                       : 1;
08628     uint32_t pf_en                        : 1;
08629     uint32_t ap_en                        : 1;
08630     uint32_t ns_en                        : 1;
08631     uint32_t mrrs                         : 3;
08632     uint32_t i_flr                        : 1;
08633     uint32_t ce_d                         : 1;
08634     uint32_t nfe_d                        : 1;
08635     uint32_t fe_d                         : 1;
08636     uint32_t ur_d                         : 1;
08637     uint32_t ap_d                         : 1;
08638     uint32_t tp                           : 1;
08639     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
08640 #endif
08641     } s;
08642     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg030_cn52xx {
08643 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
08644     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
08645     uint32_t tp                           : 1;  /**< Transaction Pending
08646                                                          Set to 1 when Non-Posted Requests are not yet completed
08647                                                          and clear when they are completed. */
08648     uint32_t ap_d                         : 1;  /**< Aux Power Detected
08649                                                          Set to 1 if Aux power detected. */
08650     uint32_t ur_d                         : 1;  /**< Unsupported Request Detected
08651                                                           Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether
08652                                                           error reporting is enabled in the Device Control register.
08653                                                          UR_D occurs when we receive something we don't support.
08654                                                          Unsupported requests are Nonfatal errors, so UR_D should
08655                                                          cause NFE_D.  Receiving a  vendor defined message should
08656                                                          cause an unsupported request. */
08657     uint32_t fe_d                         : 1;  /**< Fatal Error Detected
08658                                                           Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether
08659                                                           error reporting is enabled in the Device Control register.
08660                                                          FE_D is set if receive any of the errors in PCIE_CFG066 that
08661                                                          has a severity set to Fatal.  Malformed TLP's generally fit
08662                                                          into this category. */
08663     uint32_t nfe_d                        : 1;  /**< Non-Fatal Error detected
08664                                                           Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether
08665                                                           error reporting is enabled in the Device Control register.
08666                                                          NFE_D is set if we receive any of the errors in PCIE_CFG066
08667                                                          that has a severity set to Nonfatal and does NOT meet Advisory
08668                                                          Nonfatal criteria (PCIe 1.1 spec, Section 6.2.3.2.4), which
08669                                                          most poisoned TLP's should be. */
08670     uint32_t ce_d                         : 1;  /**< Correctable Error Detected
08671                                                           Errors are logged in this register regardless of whether
08672                                                           error reporting is enabled in the Device Control register.
08673                                                          CE_D is set if we receive any of the errors in PCIE_CFG068
08674                                                          for example a Replay Timer Timeout.  Also, it can be set if
08675                                                          we get any of the errors in PCIE_CFG066 that has a severity
08676                                                          set to Nonfatal and meets the Advisory Nonfatal criteria
08677                                                          (PCIe 1.1 spec, Section 6.2.3.2.4), which most ECRC errors
08678                                                          should be. */
08679     uint32_t reserved_15_15               : 1;
08680     uint32_t mrrs                         : 3;  /**< Max Read Request Size
08681                                                           0 = 128B
08682                                                           1 = 256B
08683                                                           2 = 512B
08684                                                           3 = 1024B
08685                                                           4 = 2048B
08686                                                           5 = 4096B
08687                                                          Note: NPEI_CTL_STATUS2[MRRS] also must be set properly.
08688                                                          NPEI_CTL_STATUS2[MRRS] must not exceed the
08689                                                          desired max read request size. */
08690     uint32_t ns_en                        : 1;  /**< Enable No Snoop */
08691     uint32_t ap_en                        : 1;  /**< AUX Power PM Enable */
08692     uint32_t pf_en                        : 1;  /**< Phantom Function Enable
08693                                                          This bit should never be set - OCTEON requests never use
08694                                                          phantom functions. */
08695     uint32_t etf_en                       : 1;  /**< Extended Tag Field Enable
08696                                                          This bit should never be set - OCTEON requests never use
08697                                                          extended tags. */
08698     uint32_t mps                          : 3;  /**< Max Payload Size
08699                                                           Legal values:
08700                                                            0  = 128B
08701                                                            1  = 256B
08702                                                           Larger sizes not supported by OCTEON.
08703                                                          Note: NPEI_CTL_STATUS2[MPS] must be set to the same
08704                                                                value for proper functionality. */
08705     uint32_t ro_en                        : 1;  /**< Enable Relaxed Ordering */
08706     uint32_t ur_en                        : 1;  /**< Unsupported Request Reporting Enable */
08707     uint32_t fe_en                        : 1;  /**< Fatal Error Reporting Enable */
08708     uint32_t nfe_en                       : 1;  /**< Non-Fatal Error Reporting Enable */
08709     uint32_t ce_en                        : 1;  /**< Correctable Error Reporting Enable */
08710 #else
08711     uint32_t ce_en                        : 1;
08712     uint32_t nfe_en                       : 1;
08713     uint32_t fe_en                        : 1;
08714     uint32_t ur_en                        : 1;
08715     uint32_t ro_en                        : 1;
08716     uint32_t mps                          : 3;
08717     uint32_t etf_en                       : 1;
08718     uint32_t pf_en                        : 1;
08719     uint32_t ap_en                        : 1;
08720     uint32_t ns_en                        : 1;
08721     uint32_t mrrs                         : 3;
08722     uint32_t reserved_15_15               : 1;
08723     uint32_t ce_d                         : 1;
08724     uint32_t nfe_d                        : 1;
08725     uint32_t fe_d                         : 1;
08726     uint32_t ur_d                         : 1;
08727     uint32_t ap_d                         : 1;
08728     uint32_t tp                           : 1;
08729     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
08730 #endif
08731     } cn52xx;

08751 /**
08752  * cvmx_pcieep#_cfg031
08753  *
08754  * This register contains the thirty-second 32-bits of PCIe type 0 configuration space.
08755  *
08756  */
08757 union cvmx_pcieepx_cfg031 {
08758     uint32_t u32;
08759     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg031_s {
08760 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
08761     uint32_t pnum                         : 8;  /**< Port number, writable through PEM()_CFG_WR. */
08762     uint32_t reserved_23_23               : 1;
08763     uint32_t aspm                         : 1;  /**< ASPM optionality compliance. */
08764     uint32_t lbnc                         : 1;  /**< Link bandwidth notification capability. Set to 0 for endpoint devices. */
08765     uint32_t dllarc                       : 1;  /**< Data link layer active reporting capable. */
08766     uint32_t sderc                        : 1;  /**< Surprise down error reporting capable. Not supported; hardwired to 0. */
08767     uint32_t cpm                          : 1;  /**< Clock power management. The default value is the value that software specifies during
08768                                                          hardware configuration, writable through PEM()_CFG_WR. However, the application must not
08769                                                          change this field. */
08770     uint32_t l1el                         : 3;  /**< L1 exit latency. The default value is the value that software specifies during hardware
08771                                                          configuration, writable through PEM()_CFG_WR. */
08772     uint32_t l0el                         : 3;  /**< L0s exit latency. The default value is the value that software specifies during hardware
08773                                                          configuration, writable through PEM()_CFG_WR. */
08774     uint32_t aslpms                       : 2;  /**< Active state link PM support. The default value is the value that software specifies
08775                                                          during hardware configuration, writable through PEM()_CFG_WR. However, the application
08776                                                          must not change this field. */
08777     uint32_t mlw                          : 6;  /**< Maximum link width.
08778                                                          The reset value of this field is determined by the value read from the PEM
08779                                                          csr PEM()_CFG[LANES4]. If LANES4 is set the reset value is 0x4, otherwise 0x2.
08780                                                          This field is writable through PEM()_CFG_WR.
08781                                                          Zeroing both [MLW] and [MLS] out of reset, using the EEPROM, will prevent the
08782                                                          link state machine from advancing past CONFIG.  This can be useful to allow
08783                                                          software to locally boot and perform preconfiguration and bug fixes.  Setting
08784                                                          [MLW] and [MLS] to nonzero values will then allow the lttsm to advance and the
08785                                                          link to come up. */
08786     uint32_t mls                          : 4;  /**< Maximum link speed. The reset value of this field is controlled by the value read from
08787                                                          PEM()_CFG[MD].
08788                                                          _ MD is 0x0, reset to 0x1: 2.5 GHz supported.
08789                                                          _ MD is 0x1, reset to 0x2: 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
08790                                                          _ MD is 0x2, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
08791                                                          _ MD is 0x3, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported (RC Mode).
08792                                                          This field is writable through PEM()_CFG_WR.
08793                                                          Zeroing both [MLW] and [MLS] out of reset, using the EEPROM, will prevent the
08794                                                          link state machine from advancing past CONFIG.  This can be useful to allow
08795                                                          software to locally boot and perform preconfiguration and bug fixes.  Setting
08796                                                          [MLW] and [MLS] to nonzero values will then allow the lttsm to advance and the
08797                                                          link to come up. */
08798 #else
08799     uint32_t mls                          : 4;
08800     uint32_t mlw                          : 6;
08801     uint32_t aslpms                       : 2;
08802     uint32_t l0el                         : 3;
08803     uint32_t l1el                         : 3;
08804     uint32_t cpm                          : 1;
08805     uint32_t sderc                        : 1;
08806     uint32_t dllarc                       : 1;
08807     uint32_t lbnc                         : 1;
08808     uint32_t aspm                         : 1;
08809     uint32_t reserved_23_23               : 1;
08810     uint32_t pnum                         : 8;
08811 #endif
08812     } s;
08813     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg031_cn52xx {
08814 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
08815     uint32_t pnum                         : 8;  /**< Port Number, writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR
08816                                                          However, the application must not change this field. */
08817     uint32_t reserved_22_23               : 2;
08818     uint32_t lbnc                         : 1;  /**< Link Bandwith Notification Capability */
08819     uint32_t dllarc                       : 1;  /**< Data Link Layer Active Reporting Capable */
08820     uint32_t sderc                        : 1;  /**< Surprise Down Error Reporting Capable
08821                                                          Not supported, hardwired to 0x0. */
08822     uint32_t cpm                          : 1;  /**< Clock Power Management
08823                                                          The default value is the value you specify during hardware
08824                                                          configuration, writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR.
08825                                                          However, the application must not change this field. */
08826     uint32_t l1el                         : 3;  /**< L1 Exit Latency
08827                                                          The default value is the value you specify during hardware
08828                                                          configuration, writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR.
08829                                                          However, the application must not change this field. */
08830     uint32_t l0el                         : 3;  /**< L0s Exit Latency
08831                                                          The default value is the value you specify during hardware
08832                                                          configuration, writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR.
08833                                                          However, the application must not change this field. */
08834     uint32_t aslpms                       : 2;  /**< Active State Link PM Support
08835                                                          The default value is the value you specify during hardware
08836                                                          configuration, writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR.
08837                                                          However, the application must not change this field. */
08838     uint32_t mlw                          : 6;  /**< Maximum Link Width
08839                                                          The default value is the value you specify during hardware
08840                                                          configuration (x1, x2, x4, x8, or x16), writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR.
08841                                                          This value will be set to 0x4 or 0x2 depending on the max
08842                                                          number of lanes (QLM_CFG == 0 set to 0x2 else 0x4). */
08843     uint32_t mls                          : 4;  /**< Maximum Link Speed
08844                                                          Default value is 0x1 for 2.5 Gbps Link.
08845                                                          This field is writable through PESC(0..1)_CFG_WR.
08846                                                          However, 0x1 is the
08847                                                          only supported value. Therefore, the application must not write
08848                                                          any value other than 0x1 to this field. */
08849 #else
08850     uint32_t mls                          : 4;
08851     uint32_t mlw                          : 6;
08852     uint32_t aslpms                       : 2;
08853     uint32_t l0el                         : 3;
08854     uint32_t l1el                         : 3;
08855     uint32_t cpm                          : 1;
08856     uint32_t sderc                        : 1;
08857     uint32_t dllarc                       : 1;
08858     uint32_t lbnc                         : 1;
08859     uint32_t reserved_22_23               : 2;
08860     uint32_t pnum                         : 8;
08861 #endif
08862     } cn52xx;

08864     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg031_cn52xx     cn56xx;

09617 /**
09618  * cvmx_pcieep#_cfg040

09620  * This register contains the forty-first 32-bits of PCIe type 0 configuration space.
09621  *
09622  */
09623 union cvmx_pcieepx_cfg040 {

09625     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg040_s {
09626 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
09627     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
09628     uint32_t ler                          : 1;  /**< Link equalization request */
09629     uint32_t ep3s                         : 1;  /**< Equalization phase 3 successful */
09630     uint32_t ep2s                         : 1;  /**< Equalization phase 2 successful */
09631     uint32_t ep1s                         : 1;  /**< Equalization phase 1 successful */
09632     uint32_t eqc                          : 1;  /**< Equalization complete */
09633     uint32_t cdl                          : 1;  /**< Current deemphasis level. When the link is operating at 5 GT/s speed, this bit reflects
09634                                                          the level of deemphasis. Encodings:
09635                                                          1 = -3.5 dB.
09636                                                          0 = -6 dB.
09637                                                          The value in this bit is undefined when the link is operating at 2.5 GT/s speed. */
09638     uint32_t cde                          : 4;  /**< Compliance deemphasis. This bit sets the deemphasis level in polling. Compliance state if
09639                                                          the entry occurred due to the TX compliance receive bit being 1. Encodings:
09640                                                          1 = -3.5 dB.
09641                                                          0 = -6 dB.
09642                                                          When the link is operating at 2.5 GT/s, the setting of this bit has no effect. */
09643     uint32_t csos                         : 1;  /**< Compliance SOS. When set to 1, the LTSSM is required to send SKP ordered sets periodically
09644                                                          in between the (modified) compliance patterns.
09645                                                          When the link is operating at 2.5 GT/s, the setting of this bit has no effect. */
09646     uint32_t emc                          : 1;  /**< Enter modified compliance. When this bit is set to 1, the device transmits a modified
09647                                                          compliance pattern if the LTSSM enters polling compliance state. */
09648     uint32_t tm                           : 3;  /**< Transmit margin. This field controls the value of the non-deemphasized voltage level at
09649                                                          the transmitter pins:
09650                                                          0x0 =  800-1200 mV for full swing 400-600 mV for half-swing.
09651                                                          0x1-0x2 = Values must be monotonic with a nonzero slope.
09652                                                          0x3 = 200-400 mV for full-swing and 100-200 mV for halfswing.
09653                                                          0x4-0x7 = Reserved.
09654                                                          This field is reset to 0x0 on entry to the LTSSM polling compliance substate. When
09655                                                          operating in 5.0 GT/s mode with full swing, the deemphasis ratio must be maintained within
09656                                                          +/- 1 dB from the specification-defined operational value either -3.5 or -6 dB. */
09657     uint32_t sde                          : 1;  /**< Selectable deemphasis. Not applicable for an upstream port or endpoint device. Hardwired to 0. */
09658     uint32_t hasd                         : 1;  /**< Hardware autonomous speed disable. When asserted, the application must disable hardware
09659                                                          from changing the link speed for device-specific reasons other than attempting to correct
09660                                                          unreliable link operation by reducing link speed. Initial transition to the highest
09661                                                          supported common link speed is not blocked by this signal. */
09662     uint32_t ec                           : 1;  /**< Enter compliance. Software is permitted to force a link to enter compliance mode at the
09663                                                          speed indicated in the target link speed field by setting this bit to 1 in both components
09664                                                          on a link and then initiating a hot reset on the link. */
09665     uint32_t tls                          : 4;  /**< Target link speed. For downstream ports, this field sets an upper limit on link
09666                                                          operational speed by restricting the values advertised by the upstream component in its
09667                                                          training sequences:
09668                                                          0x1 = 2.5 Gb/s target link speed.
09669                                                          0x2 = 5 Gb/s target link speed.
09670                                                          0x3 = 8 Gb/s target link speed.
09671                                                          All other encodings are reserved.
09672                                                          If a value is written to this field that does not correspond to a speed included in the
09673                                                          supported link speeds field, the result is undefined. For both upstream and downstream
09674                                                          ports, this field is used to set the target compliance mode speed when software is using
09675                                                          the enter compliance bit to force a link into compliance mode.
09676                                                          The reset value of this field is controlled by the value read from PEM()_CFG[MD].
09677                                                          _ MD is 0x0, reset to 0x1: 2.5 GHz supported.
09678                                                          _ MD is 0x1, reset to 0x2: 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
09679                                                          _ MD is 0x2, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported.
09680                                                          _ MD is 0x3, reset to 0x3: 8.0 GHz, 5.0 GHz and 2.5 GHz supported (RC Mode). */
09681 #else
09682     uint32_t tls                          : 4;
09683     uint32_t ec                           : 1;
09684     uint32_t hasd                         : 1;
09685     uint32_t sde                          : 1;
09686     uint32_t tm                           : 3;
09687     uint32_t emc                          : 1;
09688     uint32_t csos                         : 1;
09689     uint32_t cde                          : 4;
09690     uint32_t cdl                          : 1;
09691     uint32_t eqc                          : 1;
09692     uint32_t ep1s                         : 1;
09693     uint32_t ep2s                         : 1;
09694     uint32_t ep3s                         : 1;
09695     uint32_t ler                          : 1;
09696     uint32_t reserved_22_31               : 10;
09697 #endif
09698     } s;

12483 /**
12484  * cvmx_pcieep#_cfg452
12485  *
12486  * This register contains the four hundred fifty-third 32-bits of PCIe type 0 configuration space.
12487  *
12488  */
12489 union cvmx_pcieepx_cfg452 {
12490     uint32_t u32;
12491     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg452_s {
12492 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12493     uint32_t reserved_26_31               : 6;
12494     uint32_t eccrc                        : 1;  /**< Enable Corrupted CRC
12495                                                          Causes corrupt LCRC for TLPs when set,
12496                                                          using the pattern contained in the Other Message register.
12497                                                          This is a test feature, not to be used in normal operation. */
12498     uint32_t reserved_22_24               : 3;
12499     uint32_t lme                          : 6;  /**< Link mode enable set as follows:
12500                                                          0x1 = x1.
12501                                                          0x3 = x2.
12502                                                          0x7 = x4.
12503                                                          0xF = x8   (not supported).
12504                                                          0x1F = x16 (not supported).
12505                                                          0x3F = x32 (not supported).
12506                                                          This field indicates the maximum number of lanes supported by the PCIe port. The value can
12507                                                          be set less than 0xF to limit the number of lanes that the PCIe will attempt to use. If
12508                                                          the value of 0xF set by the hardware is not desired, this field can be programmed to a
12509                                                          smaller value (i.e. EEPROM). See also PCIEEP()_CFG031[MLW].
12510                                                          The value of this field does not indicate the number of lanes in use by the PCIe. This
12511                                                          field sets the maximum number of lanes in the PCIe core that could be used. As per the
12512                                                          PCIe specification, the PCIe core can negotiate a smaller link width, so all of x8, x4,
12513                                                          x2, and x1 are supported when
12514                                                          LME = 0xF, for example. */
12515     uint32_t reserved_12_15               : 4;
12516     uint32_t link_rate                    : 4;  /**< Reserved. */
12517     uint32_t flm                          : 1;  /**< Fast link mode. Sets all internal timers to fast mode for simulation purposes. If during
12518                                                          an EEPROM load, the first word loaded is 0xFFFFFFFF, the EEPROM load is terminated and
12519                                                          this bit is set. */
12520     uint32_t reserved_6_6                 : 1;
12521     uint32_t dllle                        : 1;  /**< DLL link enable. Enables link initialization. If DLL link enable = 0, the PCI Express bus
12522                                                          does not transmit InitFC DLLPs and does not establish a link. */
12523     uint32_t reserved_4_4                 : 1;
12524     uint32_t ra                           : 1;  /**< Reset assert. Triggers a recovery and forces the LTSSM to the hot reset state (downstream
12525                                                          port only). */
12526     uint32_t le                           : 1;  /**< Loopback enable. Initiate loopback mode as a master. On a 0->1 transition, the PCIe core
12527                                                          sends TS ordered sets with the loopback bit set to cause the link partner to enter into
12528                                                          loopback mode as a slave. Normal transmission is not possible when LE=1. To exit loopback
12529                                                          mode, take the link through a reset sequence. */
12530     uint32_t sd                           : 1;  /**< Scramble disable. Setting this bit turns off data scrambling. */
12531     uint32_t omr                          : 1;  /**< Other message request. When software writes a 1 to this bit, the PCI Express bus transmits
12532                                                          the message contained in the other message register. */
12533 #else
12534     uint32_t omr                          : 1;
12535     uint32_t sd                           : 1;
12536     uint32_t le                           : 1;
12537     uint32_t ra                           : 1;
12538     uint32_t reserved_4_4                 : 1;
12539     uint32_t dllle                        : 1;
12540     uint32_t reserved_6_6                 : 1;
12541     uint32_t flm                          : 1;
12542     uint32_t link_rate                    : 4;
12543     uint32_t reserved_12_15               : 4;
12544     uint32_t lme                          : 6;
12545     uint32_t reserved_22_24               : 3;
12546     uint32_t eccrc                        : 1;
12547     uint32_t reserved_26_31               : 6;
12548 #endif
12549     } s;
12550     struct cvmx_pcieepx_cfg452_cn52xx {
12551 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
12552     uint32_t reserved_26_31               : 6;
12553     uint32_t eccrc                        : 1;  /**< Enable Corrupted CRC
12554                                                          Causes corrupt LCRC for TLPs when set,
12555                                                          using the pattern contained in the Other Message register.
12556                                                          This is a test feature, not to be used in normal operation. */
12557     uint32_t reserved_22_24               : 3;
12558     uint32_t lme                          : 6;  /**< Link Mode Enable
12559                                                          o 000001: x1
12560                                                          o 000011: x2
12561                                                          o 000111: x4
12562                                                          o 001111: x8  (not supported)
12563                                                          o 011111: x16 (not supported)
12564                                                          o 111111: x32 (not supported)
12565                                                          This field indicates the MAXIMUM number of lanes supported
12566                                                          by the PCIe port. It is set to 0x7 or 0x3 depending
12567                                                          on the value of the QLM_CFG bits (0x7 when QLM_CFG == 0x3
12568                                                          otherwise 0x3). The value can be set less than 0x7 or 0x3
12569                                                          to limit the number of lanes the PCIe will attempt to use.
12570                                                          If the value of 0x7 or 0x3 set by the HW is not desired,
12571                                                          this field can be programmed to a smaller value (i.e. EEPROM)
12572                                                          See also MLW.
12573                                                          (Note: The value of this field does NOT indicate the number
12574                                                           of lanes in use by the PCIe. LME sets the max number of lanes
12575                                                           in the PCIe core that COULD be used. As per the PCIe specs,
12576                                                           the PCIe core can negotiate a smaller link width, so all
12577                                                           of x4, x2, and x1 are supported when LME=0x7,
12578                                                           for example.) */
12579     uint32_t reserved_8_15                : 8;
12580     uint32_t flm                          : 1;  /**< Fast Link Mode
12581                                                          Sets all internal timers to fast mode for simulation purposes.
12582                                                          If during an eeprom load, the first word loaded is 0xffffffff,
12583                                                          then the EEPROM load will be terminated and this bit will be set. */
12584     uint32_t reserved_6_6                 : 1;
12585     uint32_t dllle                        : 1;  /**< DLL Link Enable
12586                                                          Enables Link initialization. If DLL Link Enable = 0, the PCI
12587                                                          Express bus does not transmit InitFC DLLPs and does not
12588                                                          establish a Link. */
12589     uint32_t reserved_4_4                 : 1;
12590     uint32_t ra                           : 1;  /**< Reset Assert
12591                                                          Triggers a recovery and forces the LTSSM to the Hot Reset
12592                                                          state (downstream port only). */
12593     uint32_t le                           : 1;  /**< Loopback Enable
12594                                                          Initiate loopback mode as a master. On a 0->1 transition,
12595                                                          the PCIe core sends TS ordered sets with the loopback bit set
12596                                                          to cause the link partner to enter into loopback mode as a
12597                                                          slave. Normal transmission is not possible when LE=1. To exit
12598                                                          loopback mode, take the link through a reset sequence. */
12599     uint32_t sd                           : 1;  /**< Scramble Disable
12600                                                          Turns off data scrambling. */
12601     uint32_t omr                          : 1;  /**< Other Message Request
12602                                                          When software writes a `1' to this bit, the PCI Express bus
12603                                                          transmits the Message contained in the Other Message register. */
12604 #else
12605     uint32_t omr                          : 1;
12606     uint32_t sd                           : 1;
12607     uint32_t le                           : 1;
12608     uint32_t ra                           : 1;
12609     uint32_t reserved_4_4                 : 1;
12610     uint32_t dllle                        : 1;
12611     uint32_t reserved_6_6                 : 1;
12612     uint32_t flm                          : 1;
12613     uint32_t reserved_8_15                : 8;
12614     uint32_t lme                          : 6;
12615     uint32_t reserved_22_24               : 3;
12616     uint32_t eccrc                        : 1;
12617     uint32_t reserved_26_31               : 6;
12618 #endif
12619     } cn52xx;

13926                                                          phase. Encoding scheme as follows:
13927                                                          Bit [15:0] = 0x0: No preset is requested and evaluated in the EQ master phase.

13929                                                          _ 0b0000000000000000 = No preset req/evaluated in EQ master phase.
13930                                                          _ 0b00000xxxxxxxxxx1 = Preset 0 req/evaluated in EQ master phase.

13941                                                          _ All other encodings = Reserved. */

13944                                                          the PHY does not respond within 2 ms to the assertion of RxEqEval:
13945                                                          0 = Abort the current evaluation; stop any attempt to modify the remote transmitter
13946                                                          settings. Phase2 will be terminated by the 24 ms timeout.
13947                                                          1 = Ignore the 2 ms timeout and continue as normal. This is used to support PHYs that
13948                                                          require more than 2 ms to respond to the assertion of RxEqEval. */
13949     uint32_t bt                           : 1;  /**< Behavior after 24 ms timeout (when optimal settings are not found).
13950                                                          For a USP: determine the next LTSSM state from Phase2:
13951                                                          0 = Recovery.Speed.
13952                                                          1 = Recovry.Equalization.Phase3.
13953                                                          For a DSP: determine the next LTSSM state from Phase3:
13954                                                          0 = Recovery.Speed.
13955                                                          1 = Recovry.Equalization.RcrLock.
13956                                                          When optimal settings are not found:
13957                                                          * Equalization phase 3 successful status bit is not set in the link status register.
13958                                                          * Equalization phase 3 complete status bit is set in the link status register. */
13959     uint32_t fm                           : 4;  /**< Feedback mode.
13960                                                          0 = Direction of change (not supported).
13961                                                          1 = Figure of merit.
13962                                                          2-15 = Reserved. */
